title: Cleo Bardelli
description: Photo of a portrait of Cleo Bardelli, who was crowned the Queen of Wallace, Idahos Silver Jubilee. She is looking over her shoulder. This photo was used in the promotion of the citys 75th Jubilee celebration during the summer of 1958. Cleo was the daughter of Guido & Mary Bardelli of Osburn, ID.  Guido, also known as Young Firpo and the Wild Bull of Burke, who was a famed Pacific Northwest championship boxer from Burke, Idaho, in the 1920s and 1930s.
